-- Sri Lanka Wins Toss, Bats First Against England in Series Opener
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-03-26T04:22:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/sri-lanka-wins-toss-bats-first-against-england-in-series-opener.html
Sri Lanka  captain  Mahela Jayawardene  won the toss and chose to bat first against  England 
in their series-opening cricket Test in Galle.  All-rounder Samit Patel will make his Test debut for top-
ranked England, which is seeking to rebound from a 3-0 sweep of
Test losses against  Pakistan  in the United Arab Emirates in
January and February. Sri Lanka is without a Test series win
since August 2009.  SRI LANKA: Lahiru Thirimanne,  Tillakaratne Dilshan ,  Kumar
Sangakkara , Mahela Jayawardene (captain), Thilan Samaraweera,
Dinesh Chandimal, Prasanna Jayawardene, Suraj Randiv, Rangana
Herath, Suranga Lakmal, Chanaka Welegedera.  ENGLAND:  Andrew Strauss  (captain),  Alastair Cook ,  Jonathan
Trott ,  Kevin Pietersen ,  Ian Bell , Matt Prior, Samit Patel,
 Stuart Broad ,  Graeme Swann ,  James Anderson ,  Monty Panesar .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
